OL,3,C'Zero-tolerance crime zones': Will
OL,4,CLabour's crackdown plans win over
OL,5,Cvoters?
OL,7,FBack in January, a woman was attacked
OL,8,Foutside Ebony's store as she withdrew
OL,9,Fcash from the machine. She was beaten
OL,10,Fwith a bat.
OL,12,FPolice said two people were arrested
OL,13,Fand released on bail pending further
OL,14,Finvestigation. No charges have been
OL,15,Fmade.
OL,17,FEbony says she has stopped reporting a
OL,18,Flot of the incidents to the police
OL,19,Fbecause it takes so long and rarely
OL,20,Fleads to any convictions.
