OL,3,C'Zero-tolerance crime zones': Will
OL,4,CLabour's crackdown plans win over
OL,5,Cvoters?
OL,7,FEbony has never voted before. She says
OL,8,Fher family background is voting for a
OL,9,Fparty of business.
OL,11,FLike most people, she is worried about
OL,12,Fthe rising costs of living but says
OL,13,Fshe's interested to see what the main
OL,14,Fparties have to say on crime and
OL,15,Fantisocial behaviour.
OL,17,FAfter we left Ebony, we headed to a
OL,18,Fsmall local florist shop less than a
OL,19,Fmile away.
