OL,3,C'Zero-tolerance crime zones': Will
OL,4,CLabour's crackdown plans win over
OL,5,Cvoters?
OL,7,FIt seemed quite unusual for the shadow
OL,8,Fhome secretary to be launching 's plan
OL,9,Fto reduce theft and antisocial
OL,10,Fbehaviour there. But, that is where
OL,11,FYvette Cooper started her campaigning
OL,12,Fon the issue.
OL,14,FLabour's #400million plan on crime is
OL,15,Fto recruit 13,000 neighbourhood
OL,16,Fofficers, made up of 6,000 police
OL,17,Fofficers, 3000 PCSOs and 4000 special
OL,18,Fconstables to crackdown on antisocial
OL,19,Fbehaviour.
