OL,3,C'Zero-tolerance crime zones': Will
OL,4,CLabour's crackdown plans win over
OL,5,Cvoters?
OL,7,FLabour says snatch thefts of have
OL,8,Falmost doubled, from 30,000 to 58,000,
OL,9,Faccording to the Office for National
OL,10,FStatistics (ONS) from the Crime Survey
OL,11,Ffor England and Wales.
OL,13,FBut, back in 2009, when Labour was in
OL,14,Fgovernment, the figure was 97,000.
