OL,3,C'Zero-tolerance crime zones': Will
OL,4,CLabour's crackdown plans win over
OL,5,Cvoters?
OL,7,FIt is true that total thefts against
OL,8,Fthe person, as it is logged by the ONS
OL,9,Fon the National Crime Survey, have
OL,10,Fsoared from 206,000 to 321,000 with an
OL,11,Fincrease of 56% (to 321,000 incidents)
OL,12,Fcompared with the year ending December
OL,13,F2022 (206,000 incidents).
OL,15,FThe small former mining town of Maltby
OL,16,Fin South Yorkshire has issues with
OL,17,Fanti-social behaviour and theft, but
OL,18,Fperhaps what's more significant for
OL,19,Fthe Labour Party is that the
OL,20,Fparliamentary seat of Rother Valley is
OL,21,Fa must-win at this election.
